<HEAD>Italian Charity Sends Millions For African Drought Relief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Roman Catholic relief agency Caritas Italiana
said Friday it has raised more than $10 million to help the victims
of the African drought.
   The charity said $5.5 million of the $10.3 million total had
been sent to support the people in Ethiopia's Eritrea and Tigre
provinces until fall.
